1
00:00:29,250 --> 00:00:30,360
It's you.

2
00:00:30,600 --> 00:00:32,150
Why wouldn't it be me?

3
00:00:33,320 --> 00:00:35,622
Aren't you the Red-Faced Guardian
who blesses the people?

4
00:00:35,733 --> 00:00:37,220
You shouldn't be taking lives.

5
00:00:38,560 --> 00:00:40,200
The vile

6
00:00:40,800 --> 00:00:41,650
deserve to die.

7
00:00:41,920 --> 00:00:44,000
It's no reason
to stain your hands with filthy blood.

8
00:00:45,520 --> 00:00:47,710
I am avenging my friend.

9
00:00:48,860 --> 00:00:49,880
It matters not.

10
00:00:52,720 --> 00:00:53,880
Zhuang Luobai!

11
00:00:56,140 --> 00:01:02,660
=The Tang Mist S1=

12
00:02:21,300 --> 00:02:23,300
=Episode 10=

13
00:02:23,920 --> 00:02:25,320
Search everywhere!

14
00:02:25,320 --> 00:02:27,210
Find Zhuang Luobai and bring him back!

15
00:02:27,750 --> 00:02:29,040
Go! Hurry!

16
00:02:30,040 --> 00:02:30,840
Oh, Luobai...

17
00:02:31,320 --> 00:02:32,440
Where could he have gone?

18
00:02:32,490 --> 00:02:33,040
Troupe Master.

19
00:02:34,500 --> 00:02:35,300
Have you forgotten?

20
00:02:37,600 --> 00:02:39,040
Tonight is the Winter Festival.

21
00:02:41,170 --> 00:02:42,320
I am the one performing.

22
00:02:44,730 --> 00:02:46,280
Zhuang Luobai made your troupe

23
00:02:46,280 --> 00:02:47,280
the finest in Raozhou.

24
00:02:51,160 --> 00:02:52,644
I, Ming Yu, can do the exact same.

25
00:02:54,560 --> 00:02:55,320
You...

26
00:02:58,680 --> 00:02:59,880
He wasted his time raising a

27
00:02:59,880 --> 00:03:01,560
heartless wretch like you.

28
00:03:05,680 --> 00:03:06,670
Zhuang Luobai.

29
00:03:08,120 --> 00:03:10,066
The Winter Festival is
over a month away.

30
00:03:10,800 --> 00:03:12,422
My heart is no longer in the dance.

31
00:03:13,290 --> 00:03:13,900
From now on,

32
00:03:14,810 --> 00:03:15,890
let Ming Yu take my place.

33
00:03:18,640 --> 00:03:19,880
The people of this city

34
00:03:19,880 --> 00:03:21,960
only want to see you, Zhuang Luobai.

35
00:03:22,720 --> 00:03:23,720
No one else will do.

36
00:03:23,880 --> 00:03:25,400
But Ming Yu is more gifted than I am.

37
00:03:25,760 --> 00:03:26,720
He lacks for nothing,

38
00:03:27,490 --> 00:03:28,750
save for his timid nature.

39
00:03:29,040 --> 00:03:30,840
He lacks the courage
to stand up for himself.

40
00:03:31,640 --> 00:03:32,640
Over the next month,

41
00:03:33,440 --> 00:03:34,890
I will train him rigorously myself.

42
00:03:35,520 --> 00:03:36,990
I won't disappoint you, Troupe Master.

43
00:03:38,680 --> 00:03:39,510
Luobai,

44
00:03:40,120 --> 00:03:41,000
please stand up.

45
00:03:41,560 --> 00:03:42,610
As for the Winter Festival,

46
00:03:42,840 --> 00:03:44,080
we can discuss it further.

47
00:03:47,680 --> 00:03:48,480
Troupe Master,

48
00:03:49,640 --> 00:03:51,160
this Nuo opera has lasted a millennium.

49
00:03:51,880 --> 00:03:53,310
You recognized my talent.

50
00:03:53,880 --> 00:03:55,440
I must pass this kindness down.

51
00:03:56,960 --> 00:03:58,320
If you do not agree,

52
00:03:58,760 --> 00:04:00,080
I will not rise.

53
00:04:03,222 --> 00:04:05,040
If Zhuang Luobai
hadn't begged on his knees,

54
00:04:05,040 --> 00:04:06,240
someone with your meager skills

55
00:04:06,420 --> 00:04:08,000
could never have taken his place.

56
00:04:10,720 --> 00:04:11,920
For the past month,

57
00:04:12,022 --> 00:04:13,600
he has been desperate to prove to me

58
00:04:13,600 --> 00:04:14,680
that you are capable.

59
00:04:14,680 --> 00:04:15,360
Again!

60
00:04:15,360 --> 00:04:17,150
(Yet you keep making mistakes.)

61
00:04:17,880 --> 00:04:18,840
Where is your strength?

62
00:04:18,960 --> 00:04:20,160
Where is your passion?

63
00:04:20,160 --> 00:04:21,200
Where is the emotion?

64
00:04:21,240 --> 00:04:21,800
Again!

65
00:04:21,800 --> 00:04:23,190
(He was anxious that)

66
00:04:23,250 --> 00:04:24,400
(I would change my mind,)

67
00:04:24,490 --> 00:04:26,310
(so he begged me
to give you another chance.)

68
00:04:27,390 --> 00:04:28,560
(If you don't practice hard,)

69
00:04:29,200 --> 00:04:30,840
(you'll embarrass yourself on stage.)

70
00:04:31,244 --> 00:04:33,355
(If you perform
the God-Welcoming Dance this way,)

71
00:04:33,422 --> 00:04:35,970
(how can you be the lead dancer
for the Winter Festival?)

72
00:04:36,130 --> 00:04:37,980
(He hoped your new talent would shine,)

73
00:04:38,010 --> 00:04:39,311
(outshining his past glory.)

74
00:04:39,470 --> 00:04:41,320
(He wasted his time raising)

75
00:04:41,710 --> 00:04:43,840
(an ungrateful wretch like you.)

76
00:04:44,680 --> 00:04:46,360
You refuse to give me any recognition,

77
00:04:46,520 --> 00:04:48,360
but the Troupe Master values me.

78
00:04:51,111 --> 00:04:52,377
So he's replacing you with me

79
00:04:53,320 --> 00:04:54,800
for the Winter Festival.

80
00:04:58,010 --> 00:04:58,610
Troupe Master!

81
00:04:58,890 --> 00:04:59,440
Bad news!

82
00:04:59,890 --> 00:05:01,288
Master Zhuang is a murder suspect!

83
00:05:01,370 --> 00:05:02,920
The Bureau is hunting him!

84
00:05:06,355 --> 00:05:08,644
(Wangnian County Bureau)
Please see the truth, sir.

85
00:05:10,040 --> 00:05:12,720
My master is not the killer.

86
00:05:12,840 --> 00:05:14,880
Please see the truth, sir!

87
00:05:16,280 --> 00:05:18,750
Zhuang Luobai didn't kill anyone.

88
00:05:21,230 --> 00:05:21,980
Commissioner Di.

89
00:05:22,480 --> 00:05:23,880
My master is not the killer.

90
00:05:24,470 --> 00:05:25,760
I falsely accused him.

91
00:05:26,840 --> 00:05:27,720
I can prove it.

92
00:05:28,222 --> 00:05:29,888
On the night Gu Pan'er was murdered,

93
00:05:30,200 --> 00:05:32,400
Master didn't step out of his room
for a single moment.

94
00:05:33,230 --> 00:05:34,260
Because that night,

95
00:05:35,280 --> 00:05:36,840
a tall woman

96
00:05:37,480 --> 00:05:38,970
entered his room.

97
00:05:40,720 --> 00:05:42,200
They remained inside all night.

98
00:05:48,960 --> 00:05:50,920
(I thought Master
only cared about the Nuo opera)

99
00:05:51,300 --> 00:05:53,150
(and about us, his disciples.)

100
00:05:53,840 --> 00:05:55,080
I resented him for it.

101
00:05:58,680 --> 00:05:59,440
Sir.

102
00:06:01,040 --> 00:06:02,570
That day backstage,

103
00:06:03,070 --> 00:06:04,290
I purposely misled you.

104
00:06:04,680 --> 00:06:06,040
I exaggerated his strange behavior.

105
00:06:06,680 --> 00:06:08,520
He has indeed been acting weird.

106
00:06:08,520 --> 00:06:10,000
That disrupts your investigation

107
00:06:10,480 --> 00:06:11,960
and turns him into a suspect.

108
00:06:12,560 --> 00:06:13,720
I was wrong.

109
00:06:16,180 --> 00:06:17,780
The Bureau is searching for your master.

110
00:06:18,080 --> 00:06:19,150
You should join the search.

111
00:06:19,320 --> 00:06:20,590
Report to me

112
00:06:20,760 --> 00:06:21,880
the moment you find anything.

113
00:07:15,044 --> 00:07:17,040
It is indeed the tassel
from the silver hairpin.

114
00:07:17,720 --> 00:07:19,440
Why was it found inside Mrs. Gu's body?

115
00:07:22,480 --> 00:07:24,320
In the face of her daughter's death,

116
00:07:24,800 --> 00:07:26,010
this was the only way

117
00:07:26,060 --> 00:07:27,970
she could preserve the truth.

118
00:07:33,760 --> 00:07:34,720
Let's go.

119
00:07:34,720 --> 00:07:36,280
We need to see Hou Guangming.

120
00:08:09,520 --> 00:08:10,480
Vice Director Hou,

121
00:08:11,480 --> 00:08:13,080
regarding the deaths

122
00:08:13,080 --> 00:08:15,240
of your wife, Pan'er, and her parents,

123
00:08:15,520 --> 00:08:16,920
I have already unraveled the truth.

124
00:08:17,440 --> 00:08:18,640
Would you care to hear it?

125
00:08:20,760 --> 00:08:21,760
I have been

126
00:08:21,760 --> 00:08:23,440
humbly praying for you

127
00:08:23,880 --> 00:08:25,040
to solve the case, sir.

128
00:08:26,290 --> 00:08:27,170
Very well.

129
00:08:28,040 --> 00:08:30,400
Let's begin with Pan'er's mother.

130
00:08:32,200 --> 00:08:33,100
Pan'er...

131
00:08:34,280 --> 00:08:35,970
I failed you.

132
00:08:37,120 --> 00:08:37,830
I have

133
00:08:38,270 --> 00:08:40,000
failed to protect you.

134
00:08:46,910 --> 00:08:48,720
You accursed woman.

135
00:08:49,360 --> 00:08:52,640
What are you staring at me for?

136
00:08:54,000 --> 00:08:55,640
Why haven't you cooked dinner?

137
00:08:57,280 --> 00:08:58,860
She's already dead!

138
00:08:58,890 --> 00:09:00,850
Why are you keeping
her things? It's bad luck!

139
00:09:01,480 --> 00:09:03,410
Pan'er was your daughter.

140
00:09:03,640 --> 00:09:05,920
Your own flesh and blood!

141
00:09:06,120 --> 00:09:06,880
Hmph.

142
00:09:07,610 --> 00:09:09,400
She's dead and gone.

143
00:09:10,900 --> 00:09:11,920
I...

144
00:09:12,470 --> 00:09:14,120
What do you expect me to do about it?

145
00:09:20,880 --> 00:09:22,940
If it can be traded for silver,

146
00:09:24,200 --> 00:09:25,800
isn't that a good thing?

147
00:09:25,840 --> 00:09:27,320
You're going to gamble again!

148
00:09:27,690 --> 00:09:29,170
It's Pan'er's belongings!

149
00:09:29,750 --> 00:09:31,840
- Give it to me!
- Let go!

150
00:09:36,310 --> 00:09:37,500
As a mother,

151
00:09:37,720 --> 00:09:40,200
I couldn't even protect my own child.

152
00:09:42,560 --> 00:09:43,920
I am going to the Bureau

153
00:09:44,500 --> 00:09:45,760
to report you all!

154
00:09:47,520 --> 00:09:48,950
You accursed woman!

155
00:09:52,370 --> 00:09:53,920
You worthless piece of trash.

156
00:09:54,720 --> 00:09:57,000
If you dare
take a single step out of this room,

157
00:09:57,760 --> 00:09:59,400
I'll rip you apart!

158
00:10:00,640 --> 00:10:03,400
You couldn't even give me a son,
you useless wife.

159
00:10:04,000 --> 00:10:06,640
If you had an ounce of beauty left,

160
00:10:08,080 --> 00:10:09,840
I would have sold you off

161
00:10:09,840 --> 00:10:11,360
for cash a long time ago.

162
00:10:15,160 --> 00:10:15,960
Give it to me!

163
00:10:16,620 --> 00:10:17,760
Give it here!

164
00:10:26,480 --> 00:10:28,650
Stop right there, you miserable woman!

165
00:10:29,120 --> 00:10:30,800
Inside Mrs. Gu's stomach,

166
00:10:30,800 --> 00:10:32,850
we discovered this tassel
from the silver hairpin.

167
00:10:33,280 --> 00:10:34,560
By doing this,

168
00:10:34,600 --> 00:10:36,960
she must have
known the truth about Pan'er's death.

169
00:10:37,560 --> 00:10:39,050
But as a mere woman,

170
00:10:39,060 --> 00:10:41,090
she was powerless
against a desperate gambler.

171
00:10:41,920 --> 00:10:43,440
This was her only way to fight back.

172
00:10:43,680 --> 00:10:44,400
Master,

173
00:10:45,000 --> 00:10:47,160
why didn't the killer
dispose of the weapon

174
00:10:47,320 --> 00:10:48,840
or make it disappear forever?

175
00:10:49,000 --> 00:10:50,240
How did Gu Qi get it?

176
00:10:50,760 --> 00:10:52,280
There is only one explanation.

177
00:10:53,200 --> 00:10:55,600
Gu Qi had long
been consumed by gambling,

178
00:10:55,910 --> 00:10:57,470
and had run up massive debts.

179
00:10:57,800 --> 00:10:59,770
Once he discovered
that this silver hairpin

180
00:10:59,830 --> 00:11:01,280
was the weapon used in the murder,

181
00:11:01,360 --> 00:11:04,170
he used it to extort money
for his gambling habits.

182
00:11:04,400 --> 00:11:05,720
Di is right.

183
00:11:05,760 --> 00:11:06,560
A few days ago,

184
00:11:06,560 --> 00:11:07,620
Gu Qi did indeed

185
00:11:07,640 --> 00:11:09,120
pay off a substantial gambling debt.

186
00:11:10,000 --> 00:11:11,200
Are you implying that

187
00:11:12,240 --> 00:11:13,960
my father-in-law killed his wife?

188
00:11:14,120 --> 00:11:14,880
No.

189
00:11:15,400 --> 00:11:17,000
Gu Qi only wanted leverage.

190
00:11:17,280 --> 00:11:18,520
Only the killer

191
00:11:18,520 --> 00:11:20,160
wants to take a life.

192
00:11:20,800 --> 00:11:22,080
Stop right there!

193
00:11:23,000 --> 00:11:24,480
Get back here!

194
00:11:32,280 --> 00:11:33,000
Who are...

195
00:11:33,640 --> 00:11:34,400
Who are you?

196
00:11:36,760 --> 00:11:37,830
Hey!

197
00:11:38,290 --> 00:11:39,680
Hey!

198
00:11:44,280 --> 00:11:46,000
Take this to pay off your gambling debts.

199
00:11:55,400 --> 00:11:56,800
It was Zhuang Luobai.

200
00:11:57,840 --> 00:11:59,640
How could he be so ruthless?

201
00:11:59,680 --> 00:12:00,320
Not so fast.

202
00:12:00,760 --> 00:12:02,200
Traces of a hallucinogen were found

203
00:12:02,200 --> 00:12:03,760
inside Gu Qi's stomach.

204
00:12:04,040 --> 00:12:05,080
Mind-altering powder.

205
00:12:05,120 --> 00:12:05,840
Exactly.

206
00:12:05,840 --> 00:12:06,840
A massive dose.

207
00:12:06,920 --> 00:12:09,850
And it must have been
slipped into the liquor he drank.

208
00:12:25,960 --> 00:12:27,640
The killer knew he was a gambler,

209
00:12:27,760 --> 00:12:29,480
and that he had a guilty conscience.

210
00:12:29,800 --> 00:12:32,180
To put an end to his endless extortion,

211
00:12:32,400 --> 00:12:33,840
once his false testimony

212
00:12:33,840 --> 00:12:35,160
was no longer of any use,

213
00:12:35,200 --> 00:12:37,600
a mind-altering powder
drew out his inner demons,

214
00:12:37,800 --> 00:12:40,280
causing Gu Qi to scare himself to death.

215
00:12:41,080 --> 00:12:42,200
Finally,

216
00:12:42,480 --> 00:12:44,000
the deaths of Gu Qi and his wife

217
00:12:44,130 --> 00:12:45,880
were blamed

218
00:12:45,880 --> 00:12:46,600
on the curse

219
00:12:46,600 --> 00:12:48,640
of the Red-Faced Guardian.

220
00:12:50,280 --> 00:12:51,160
False testimony?

221
00:12:53,560 --> 00:12:54,880
I may be simple-minded,

222
00:12:55,560 --> 00:12:56,760
but even I can tell

223
00:12:57,600 --> 00:12:59,720
that you are suspecting me, sir.

224
00:13:00,200 --> 00:13:01,160
I never suspect

225
00:13:01,160 --> 00:13:03,480
anyone without reason.

226
00:13:03,800 --> 00:13:06,200
The footprints at the scene
where Pan'er's body was found...

227
00:13:06,210 --> 00:13:08,080
The foot length is 27.33 cm.

228
00:13:08,120 --> 00:13:09,177
It does not match yours.

229
00:13:09,240 --> 00:13:11,920
At first,
I believed the killer was left-handed.

230
00:13:12,450 --> 00:13:13,880
He is left-handed.

231
00:13:14,520 --> 00:13:15,840
It also does not match you.

232
00:13:16,320 --> 00:13:19,280
But then, Qinglan made a new discovery.

233
00:13:19,400 --> 00:13:20,680
During the autopsy, I found

234
00:13:21,120 --> 00:13:22,600
that Pan'er herself was left-handed.

235
00:13:22,760 --> 00:13:25,480
That was when I came to a realization.

236
00:13:25,480 --> 00:13:27,040
I realized

237
00:13:27,040 --> 00:13:28,440
how Pan'er died.

238
00:13:30,288 --> 00:13:32,120
I don't care
who you are running away with.

239
00:13:32,720 --> 00:13:33,680
Remember that

240
00:13:33,680 --> 00:13:35,640
I bought and paid for you.

241
00:13:35,920 --> 00:13:36,920
Please let me go.

242
00:13:37,840 --> 00:13:38,960
I beg you.

243
00:13:39,100 --> 00:13:40,560
I will return your money.

244
00:13:43,080 --> 00:13:44,240
What are you doing?

245
00:13:46,800 --> 00:13:49,720
Playing the unyielding martyr?

246
00:13:53,280 --> 00:13:54,080
Stab yourself then!

247
00:13:54,760 --> 00:13:56,520
Go on, stab!

248
00:14:09,620 --> 00:14:10,600
Even in death,

249
00:14:11,920 --> 00:14:13,920
you belong to me.

250
00:14:17,560 --> 00:14:19,000
That was when

251
00:14:19,880 --> 00:14:21,160
he appeared.

252
00:14:30,200 --> 00:14:32,160
My daughter!

253
00:14:33,390 --> 00:14:34,210
You...

254
00:14:34,640 --> 00:14:36,280
You'll pay for her death!

255
00:14:43,920 --> 00:14:45,360
So what if you're rich?

256
00:14:45,800 --> 00:14:47,560
Does having money
give you the right to...

257
00:15:29,480 --> 00:15:30,760
To think such a vile beast

258
00:15:31,720 --> 00:15:34,360
existed under my jurisdiction.

259
00:15:34,360 --> 00:15:36,400
Gu Qi watched
his own flesh and blood get murdered,

260
00:15:36,400 --> 00:15:37,688
yet for the sake of money,

261
00:15:37,755 --> 00:15:39,440
he helped cover up the crimes.

262
00:15:39,560 --> 00:15:40,480
He is even worse.

263
00:15:41,000 --> 00:15:41,880
Vice Director Hou,

264
00:15:42,540 --> 00:15:44,200
is my deduction correct?

265
00:15:44,960 --> 00:15:45,640
Sir,

266
00:15:45,822 --> 00:15:47,840
this is nothing
but mere speculation on your part.

267
00:15:48,680 --> 00:15:49,680
Do you have any evidence?

268
00:15:50,760 --> 00:15:52,000
If not,

269
00:15:52,240 --> 00:15:53,320
then please,

270
00:15:53,840 --> 00:15:56,160
do not simply
abuse your authority to intimidate me.

271
00:16:09,720 --> 00:16:11,630
Wearing shoes that do not fit,

272
00:16:12,200 --> 00:16:14,350
aren't you afraid of taking a fall?

273
00:16:16,860 --> 00:16:17,980
(Preview of Next Episode)

274
00:16:19,240 --> 00:16:21,880
You desired nothing more than
to become the Red-Faced Guardian.

275
00:16:23,320 --> 00:16:25,740
Today, your wish is granted.

276
00:16:26,960 --> 00:16:27,920
Take it off.

277
00:16:28,422 --> 00:16:29,630
You will find your true self

278
00:16:31,130 --> 00:16:32,560
and become who you are meant to be.

279
00:16:33,520 --> 00:16:35,190
The Guardian has come for me.

280
00:16:36,240 --> 00:16:38,050
The Guardian has come for me!

281
00:16:47,550 --> 00:16:49,130
♪Night covers the long streets♪

282
00:16:50,210 --> 00:16:51,920
♪The city remains silent♪

283
00:16:53,310 --> 00:16:54,900
♪Wind turns the old pages♪

284
00:16:55,160 --> 00:16:57,400
♪Words still left unspoken♪

285
00:16:58,800 --> 00:17:00,440
♪Bloodstains still hold their warmth♪

286
00:17:01,570 --> 00:17:04,040
♪Lamplight slowly tilts aside♪

287
00:17:04,660 --> 00:17:06,140
♪Who hides in the shadows♪

288
00:17:06,140 --> 00:17:09,280
♪Still circling around the truth?♪

289
00:17:09,900 --> 00:17:11,820
♪Love is born from desire♪

290
00:17:12,510 --> 00:17:14,640
♪Hatred rises out of greed♪

291
00:17:15,780 --> 00:17:17,440
♪One thought becomes a snare♪

292
00:17:17,440 --> 00:17:20,740
♪A lifetime trapped within♪

293
00:17:22,190 --> 00:17:23,510
♪Someone once warned me♪

294
00:17:23,510 --> 00:17:25,030
♪To stop upon this shore♪

295
00:17:25,030 --> 00:17:26,350
♪But sunlight burns too fiercely♪

296
00:17:26,350 --> 00:17:27,840
♪Fragile eyes break too easily♪

297
00:17:27,840 --> 00:17:28,960
♪If one thought retreats♪

298
00:17:28,960 --> 00:17:30,260
♪Then all things rest in peace♪

299
00:17:30,260 --> 00:17:31,600
♪But in this world♪

300
00:17:31,600 --> 00:17:34,000
♪Who will make the final judgment?♪

301
00:17:35,830 --> 00:17:38,640
♪If truth is cold as a frosted blade♪

302
00:17:38,640 --> 00:17:40,110
♪Still I walk ahead♪

303
00:17:40,340 --> 00:17:41,560
♪Let it pierce through♪

304
00:17:41,560 --> 00:17:46,300
♪The illusions before my eyes♪

305
00:17:46,300 --> 00:17:48,540
♪Layer upon layer of deception♪

306
00:17:48,540 --> 00:17:49,940
♪Covering every heart♪

307
00:17:49,940 --> 00:17:51,130
♪How many people♪

308
00:17:51,390 --> 00:17:52,760
♪Weave their own cocoon♪

309
00:17:52,760 --> 00:17:54,970
♪Yet call it♪

310
00:17:55,170 --> 00:17:56,510
♪Fate?♪

311
00:17:56,870 --> 00:17:58,050
♪Life and death♪

312
00:17:58,050 --> 00:17:59,310
♪Balanced on a single line♪

313
00:17:59,660 --> 00:18:00,830
♪Light and shadow♪

314
00:18:00,830 --> 00:18:02,090
♪Hanging side by side♪

315
00:18:02,090 --> 00:18:03,570
♪Goodness is not absolute♪

316
00:18:03,570 --> 00:18:04,980
♪Nor is evil ever complete♪

317
00:18:04,980 --> 00:18:06,520
♪In the end, it is only♪

318
00:18:06,520 --> 00:18:07,900
♪A single misguided thought♪

319
00:18:07,900 --> 00:18:09,460
♪If unveiling the truth♪

320
00:18:09,460 --> 00:18:10,800
♪Requires abandoning tenderness♪

321
00:18:10,800 --> 00:18:11,970
♪Then this answer♪

322
00:18:11,970 --> 00:18:13,330
♪Can it still remain true?♪

323
00:18:13,330 --> 00:18:14,730
♪When love and law♪

324
00:18:14,730 --> 00:18:16,210
♪Stand against each other in silence♪

325
00:18:16,210 --> 00:18:17,610
♪Which figure before me♪

326
00:18:17,610 --> 00:18:24,810
♪Am I meant to believe?♪

327
00:18:24,810 --> 00:18:27,540
♪If truth is cold as a frosted blade♪

328
00:18:27,540 --> 00:18:29,130
♪Still I walk ahead♪

329
00:18:29,130 --> 00:18:30,370
♪Not for fame or glory♪

330
00:18:30,370 --> 00:18:35,240
♪Nor caring who wins or loses♪

331
00:18:35,240 --> 00:18:37,050
♪Human nature is clouded♪

332
00:18:37,050 --> 00:18:38,770
♪Yet still reflects the stars♪

333
00:18:38,770 --> 00:18:40,240
♪Though this world♪

334
00:18:40,240 --> 00:18:41,610
♪Is filled with mud and mire♪

335
00:18:41,610 --> 00:18:43,860
♪There is still a light♪

336
00:18:43,860 --> 00:18:46,820
♪Worth pursuing♪

337
00:18:46,820 --> 00:18:48,640
♪Every case has its ending♪

338
00:18:48,640 --> 00:18:49,900
♪But night does not always fade♪

339
00:18:50,170 --> 00:18:51,550
♪The wind stops, the pages close♪

340
00:18:51,550 --> 00:18:52,770
♪Yet hearts remain unsettled♪

341
00:18:53,040 --> 00:18:54,120
♪If justice stands♪

342
00:18:54,120 --> 00:18:55,370
♪Without mercy beside it♪

343
00:18:55,370 --> 00:18:57,170
♪Then how is it♪

344
00:18:57,170 --> 00:19:06,730
♪Any different from a blade?♪

345
00:19:06,730 --> 00:19:09,920
♪If truth is cold as a frosted blade♪

346
00:19:09,920 --> 00:19:11,400
♪Still I walk ahead♪

347
00:19:11,400 --> 00:19:12,790
♪Even if the world♪

348
00:19:12,790 --> 00:19:17,520
♪Refuses to answer♪

349
00:19:17,520 --> 00:19:19,480
♪When every hidden truth♪

350
00:19:19,480 --> 00:19:21,190
♪Finally reveals itself♪

351
00:19:21,190 --> 00:19:22,550
♪I only wish♪

352
00:19:22,550 --> 00:19:24,030
♪To hold on♪

353
00:19:24,030 --> 00:19:28,770
♪Within the darkness♪

354
00:19:28,770 --> 00:19:30,770
♪To the heart♪

